laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout with no evidence of focal lesions; no intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation; gallbladder within normal limits; pancreas has normal attenuation throughout with no evidence of focal lesions; spleen shows normal size and attenuation with no focal lesions; kidneys are of normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram; small hiatal hernia present; inflamed and enlarged appendix measuring up to 8 mm with adjacent fat stranding and reactive mesenteric lymph nodes; a small appendicalith noted; no evidence of perforation or abscess formation.
